allTags().return: All of the deployed version tags.

appeal(uint256,bytes).details: Appeals a ruling to the current `implementation` contract.

params._extraData: Can be used to give extra info on the appeal.
params._localDisputeID: The ID of the dispute to be appealed.

appealCost(uint256,bytes).details: Computes the cost of appealing to the current `implementation` contract. It is recommended not to increase it often, as it can be highly time and gas consuming for the arbitrated contracts to cope with fee augmentation.

params._extraData: Can be used to give additional info on the dispute to be created.
params._localDisputeID: The ID of the dispute to be appealed.

appealPeriod(uint256).details: Compute the start and end of the dispute's current or next appeal period, if possible.
appealPeriod(uint256).return: The start and end of the period.

arbitrationCost(bytes).details: Computes the cost of arbitration in the current `implementation` contract. It is recommended not to increase it often, as it can be highly time and gas consuming for the arbitrated contracts to cope with fee augmentation.

params._extraData: Can be used to give additional info on the dispute to be created.

createDispute(uint256,bytes).details: Creates a dispute in the current `implementation` contract. Must be called by the arbitrable contract.

params._choices: The amount of choices the arbitrator can make in this dispute.
params._extraData: Can be used to give additional info on the dispute to be created.

createDispute(uint256,bytes).return: The ID of the created dispute in the context of this contract.

currentRuling(uint256).details: Get the current ruling of a dispute. This is useful for parties to know if they should appeal.
currentRuling(uint256).return: _ruling The current ruling which will be given if there is no appeal or which has been given.

disputeStatus(uint256).details: Get the status of a dispute.

params._nextAddress: The next address of the managed contract.

rollback().return: True if there was a previous version and the rollback succeeded, false otherwise.

rule(uint256,uint256).details: Give a ruling for a dispute. Must be called by the arbitrator. The purpose of this function is to ensure that the address calling it has the right to rule on the contract.

params._externalDisputeID: ID of the dispute in the Arbitrator contract.
params._ruling: Ruling given by the arbitrator. Note that 0 is reserved for "Not able/wanting to make a decision".

publish(bytes32,address).notice: Publishes the next version of the managed contract, `nextTag`, at `nextAddress`.

rollback().notice: Rolls back 'stable' to the previous deployment, and returns true, if one exists, returns false otherwise.

setStable(bytes32).notice: Sets the value of 'stable' to the address of `nextTag`.
